definitions.definition: The process of interpreting written language .
examples: The student is behind in his reading by several chapters.
That's my reading of the current situation.

subdefinitions.definition: The process of interpreting a symbol , a sign or a measuring device.

definitions.definition: A value indicated by a measuring device.
examples: He glanced across and took note of the speedometer reading .

definitions.definition: An event at which written material is read aloud .
A pronunciation associated with a particular character or word ; particularly in East Asian scripts .
examples: Some Chinese characters have numerous readings .

definitions.definition: The extent of what one has read.
examples: He's a man of good reading .

definitions.definition: One of several stages a bill passes through before becoming law.
A piece of literature or passage of scripture read aloud to an audience.
examples: After the homily there will be two readings from the Bible.

definitions.definition: The content of a reading list .
The act or process of imagining sequences of potential moves and responses without actually placing stones.
